      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ENERGISER DASH (1) comes off an average run last start when seventh at this track over 425m behind Rae's Rainbow (24.90) in a Bottom Up - Grade 5. Should bounce back. PAW INGRID (8) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by a nose at Geelong in a handy 22.90 beating Aston Transcend. Can make it back-to-back wins. MCIVOR JEWELS (2) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing sixth (24.88) in a Bottom Up - Grade 5 at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning three races. Warrants plenty of respect. DERNANCOURT (3) cannot be left out after placing last start.",
